# DMS RULES — NON-NEGOTIABLE
Read this file at the start of every task. This is the single source of truth for all agents rules.



## EXECUTION
No questions unless blocked. No placeholders/TODOs. Fix failures before proceeding.
Tests: `npm run test:dealer` (Jest only — no Vitest/Playwright).
Slice order: schema → db → service → api → ui → tests.
New features: read /docs/canonical/INDEX.md first.

## STACK (PINNED — no upgrades without approval)
Next.js 16.1.6 · React 19.2.4 · TypeScript strict · Prisma 6.7.0 · Supabase · Zod 3.25.76 · shadcn/ui · Node 24.x

## STRUCTURE
apps/dealer/       Main dealer app (Next.js App Router)
apps/platform/     Platform admin app
apps/mobile/       React Native (Expo)
packages/contracts Shared Zod schemas + types
modules/<m>/       db/ service/ ui/ tests/
lib/               auth, tenant, rbac, db, money, events, api handlers

## LAYERS
✓ route → service → db → Prisma
✗ route → Prisma | UI → service | service → UI | module-A-db → module-B-db
Cross-module: service-to-service or domain events only.

## MULTI-TENANCY
- Every business table: dealership_id (UUID non-null) + created_at + updated_at
- All queries scoped by ctx.dealershipId (session — never client input)
- Cross-tenant ID → 404 NOT_FOUND (never 403)

## API ROUTES
Pattern: getAuthContext → guardPermission → validate → service → jsonResponse
Imports from @/lib/api/handler: getAuthContext, guardPermission, handleApiError, jsonResponse, getRequestMeta
ZodError → validationErrorResponse(e.issues) status 400 | export const dynamic = "force-dynamic"
Error shape: { error: { code, message, details } } — no stack traces
Codes: UNAUTHORIZED FORBIDDEN NOT_FOUND VALIDATION_ERROR CONFLICT RATE_LIMITED INTERNAL
Platform routes: requirePlatformAdmin() first. Non-platform → 403 (never 404).
Rate-limit: auth, VIN decode, file upload, finance session.

## RBAC
guardPermission(ctx, "module.action") on every route — no bypass, no admin exceptions.
Permissions: inventory.read/write · deals.read/write · finance.read · reports.export · admin.roles.write
the DMS uses domain.read and domain.write as the default permission model. Subfamily permissions are allowed only where the codebase already enforces a real bounded workflow or action family.

## PRISMA
PK: `id String @id @default(uuid()) @db.Uuid`
Columns: snake_case via @map. Soft delete: deletedAt DateTime?, deletedBy String?
Multi-step: prisma.$transaction(). Lists: take max 100 (except jobs/exports/analytics).
Indexes: dealership_id + FKs + status + created_at. Composite: @@index([dealershipId, status])
New model requires: id · dealershipId · createdAt · updatedAt · indexes · deletedAt (critical) · Dealership relation.

## N+1
✗ for-loop + findMany. ✓ include / select / createMany / deleteMany / Promise.all batches.

## MONEY
DB: BigInt cents. API: string cents. UI: lib/money.ts display only — never math.
✗ float/decimal/number for currency.
Imports: formatCents, parseDollarsToCents from @/lib/money

## DOMAIN EVENTS
Imports: emitEvent, registerListener from @/lib/infrastructure/events/eventBus
Payloads must include dealershipId. Handlers must be idempotent.
Listeners: fire-and-forget — Promise.resolve().then(() => listener(payload))
✗ custom emitters, raw Node EventEmitter outside infrastructure/events.

## CACHE
Import: withCache from @/lib/infrastructure/cache/cacheHelpers
Key format: <domain>:<dealershipId>:<resource> via cacheKeys.ts — no raw strings.
TTL required: dashboard 10-30s · reports 20-60s · inventory 10-30s · CRM 10-20s
✓ Cache: aggregated dashboard, reporting, heavy lists.
✗ Cache: single entity reads, RBAC, auth, mutations in fetchers.
Invalidation: vehicle.created/updated → inventory+dashboard · deal.sold → dashboard+reports · customer.created → CRM

## AUDIT
Import: auditLog from @/lib/audit
Required on create/update/delete: Vehicle · Customer · Deal · DealFinance · FinanceApplication · Document · Role · Membership · DealershipInvite · platform writes · signed URL access
Metadata ✗: SSN, DOB, income, email, phone, tokens, passwords, card data.

## UI
Components: shadcn/ui only (@/components/ui/*) — ✗ MUI/Chakra/Mantine/Ant/Bootstrap.
Colors: CSS vars only — bg-[var(--surface)] text-[var(--text)] border-[var(--border)]
Primary buttons: use --primary/--primary-hover (deeper blue), NOT --accent. Button component variant="primary" already uses it. Inline-styled CTAs must use bg-[var(--primary)] text-white hover:bg-[var(--primary-hover)]. --accent stays for decorative elements (links, rings, badges, sidebar).
Tokens: import { dashboardCard, severityBadgeClasses, widgetRowSurface } from "@/lib/ui/tokens"
Texture: cards use surface-noise via cardBase (DMSCard); table shells use surface-noise via tableTokens.shell; KPI/metric cards use kpi-noise.
Every screen: loading + empty + error states.
Forms: React Hook Form + Zod, inline errors, disable on submit.
Tables: parsePagination from @/lib/api/pagination, default 25, max 100.
AppShell: only in apps/dealer/app/(app)/layout.tsx. ModalShell: never self-closing.

## SECURITY
✗ Store: SSN, DOB, income, raw card data, passwords.
Uploads: mime allowlist, max 25MB, no path traversal, paths prefixed by dealershipId.
Downloads: signed URLs only, audit every issuance (file.accessed).
Platform admin: DB-backed (PlatformAdmin table) — not cookie-only.

## DEAL IMMUTABILITY
status === CONTRACTED: no edits to financial fields, fees, trades. Only → CANCELED. Return 409. Enforce in service.

## BACKGROUND JOBS
BullMQ/Redis is the active queue implementation in this repo. Vercel Cron is still appropriate for light scheduled tasks.
Payloads: include dealershipId. One tenant per job. Idempotent. Retry-safe.

## QUERY COMPLEXITY
>10k rows: paginate, aggregate, or stream. ✗ full table loads.

## NEVER
float math for money · SSN/DOB/card storage · unscoped queries · skip guardPermission
AppShell outside layout.tsx · Tailwind palette colors · MUI/Chakra/Mantine
unbounded list queries · stack traces to clients · client-supplied dealership_id
cross-module DB imports · business logic in UI · PII in audit metadata
mutations on CONTRACTED deal · Vitest/Playwright · custom event emitters
raw cache keys · infinite TTL · cache single-entity/auth/RBAC reads
